{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/game-gedhara-nugegoda/review-175171", "name": "Gami Gedara (Nugegoda)", "excerpt": "Somewhere in the heart of Nugegoda, by the highway, there's a shop that serves up some amazing rice and curry. We went to check them out for lunch because why not?", "yamu_review": ["Gami\u00a0Gedara (\u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2 \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dbb) offers a buffet-style dining experience. From Mixed Rice to Biriyani to Rice and Curry, their food is as fresh as it is good.\u00a0", "What makes this place special is it's rather mod interior and their smart use of compartment-trays on which your food is served. It's the little things that make something stand out.\u00a0", "The Rice and Curry (Rs. 160 for the veg option) is served buffet-style. You get to pick and choose what curries you want, what rice you'd prefer etc. Our curries of choice consisted of ", " ", ", ", ", beetroot, dhal, onion salad and of course; ", ". Each curry was fresh and seasoned adequately.", "\r\nThe red rice had a rich, nutty flavour coming through which complimented the add-ons.", "\r\nIt's healthy, so that's an added bonus.", "The Mixed Rice (Rs. 350) was basically bits of sausage, chicken and vegetables incorporated into fried rice. By default you are served\u00a0portions of chop suey, coleslaw, gravy and chilli paste but you can switch them up as you wish and also pick your meat of choice.", "\r\nVishvi opted for a hefty helping of pork and her verdict was positive. She says the pork was soft, spicy and there was actual meat as opposed to the usual chunks of fat.", "\r\n", "The Biriyani (Rs. 350)\u00a0isn't traditional biriyani, but it's still very good. The rice tasted like chicken stock, came with chopped cilantro and plenty of caramelised onions scattered about. The chicken was a little tough on the outside but soft on the inside.", "\r\nIt didn't shine and was rather bland but we're not complaining.", "\r\nThe egg was just added on for decorative purposes as it was extremely rubbery, so we didn't bother with that.\u00a0", "Service is pretty much DIY. You order over the counter, help yourself to drinks from the fridge and pay\u00a0at said counter once you're done eating. Mysteriously enough there are a LOT of people hanging out behind the counter so they aren't under-staffed.\u00a0", "The place is cute, with wooden tables and chairs painted bright colours like blue and green. The counter is presented in true local style with clay pots and banana leaves used as utensils.", "\r\nIt was unbearaby hot and stuffy inside, but they fixed that by turning the AC on. The AC was leaky but they fixed that by not acknowledging it.\u00a0", "If you're ever in Nugegoda around lunch time, head to Gami Gedara. Their food is top-notch and you'll get your money's worth.\u00a0", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Gami Gedara is a little eatery in Nugegoda. They serve up some good rice and curry, so we spent our lunch-break here.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0db1\u0dd4\u0d9c\u0dda\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0da9 \u0dc4\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a \u0db6\u0dad\u0dca \u0db6\u0da9\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d86\u0dc0\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca, \u0d94\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dc4\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dba\u0ddd \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca.\n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            Great tasting food and good portions! The place is small and gets busy during lunch so you need to get in early but it's well worth it for the price. ", "\nIt's right next to the road at nugegoda junction but the area itself is sealed so the food and eating areas are protected from the dust. Thumbs up for hygiene!\n                                    ", "\n                                            Went there for lunch on Sunday and I'm proud to report that they haven't declined in quality at all.", "\r\nIn fact, they're super crowded, so make sure you go early.", "\r\nThey've even got a live band playing! \n                                    ", "\n                                            ", "\n                                    "], "user_comments": [], "contact": "Call 0112821377", "address": "No. 150, Piyadasa Hewavitharana Building, High Level Road, Nugegoda ", "directions": "It's on the right side of High Level Road. Don't take the fly-over.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["11:30 AM \u2013 09:30 PM", "11:30 AM \u2013 09:30 PM", "11:30 AM \u2013 09:30 PM", "11:30 AM \u2013 09:30 PM", "11:30 AM \u2013 09:30 PM", "11:30 AM \u2013 09:30 PM", "11:30 AM \u2013 09:30 PM"], "cuisine": ["Sri Lankan"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 200 - Rs. 500", "dishes": ["Biriyani", "Rice And Curry", "Pork"], "overall_rating": "4", "quality_rating": "4", "service_rating": "3", "ambience_rating": "4", "near_by_places_names": ["Namaste", "Sahan Agro Strawberry Corner", "Shu Limit", "Ambul Thiyal", "My Burger"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["237 High Level Road, Nugegoda", "Jambugasmulla Mawatha, Nugegoda", "142 S. De S. Jayasinghe Mw (N