{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/klassy-pastry-shop/review-5608", "name": "Klassy Pastry Shop ", "excerpt": "Klassy is a really good pastry shop - reliable for savouries and milk toffees. ", "yamu_review": ["\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Klassy is a really good pastry shop - reliable for savouries and milk toffees. \n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Klassy, on the corner of De Fonseka Road and Dickmans Road, is a Havelock Town classic. Serving up the staples of Ceylan Tapas - Patties, pan-rolls, bacon and egg pastry, seeni sambol buns, eclairs,(Rs 40-80) with iced coffee in an unpretentious location this place attracts the great, the good, the average and everyone else of Havelock Town.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dca\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dca \u0da7\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dda, \u0da9\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dca\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dda, \u0daf \u0dc6\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dda\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dda \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd2 '\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dd2' \u0da7\u0ddc\u0db4\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd1\u0db8 \u0d94\u0db6\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db1\u0db8\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf. \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0da7\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9c \u0dc0\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca, \u0db4\u0dd1\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbb\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dca, \u0db6\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dcf \u0db6\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb \u0db4\u0dda\u0dc3\u0dca\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2, \u0dc3\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0db6\u0ddd\u0dbd \u0db6\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca, \u0d89\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dda \u0dbb\u0dd4. 40 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7 80 \u0daf\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dca, \u0d85\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca. \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd4\u0da9\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dad\u0dca, \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dca\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dca \u0da7\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dda \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0db8 \u0db8\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0db8\u0d9a\u0db8 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0da7 \u0d86\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc1\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf. \n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            One of the most disappointing places I've ever been to. in my first experience i bought a vegetable roll but the roll was dry and frozen. This made it hard to eat and there wasn't enough stuffing also however the prices were high", "\n\n                                    ", "\n                                            O stars , O rating\u2026  given to Klassy Colombo 4 outlet in De Fonseka Road. I am a regular customer to Klassy Colombo Branch, Myself and my Family  visit there every Friday for sure and also another within the week too. ", "\r\nI had a bad experience in buying a Ribbon Cake from Klassy on 5th of May 2017, while buying it I was advise the cake was made same day morning by the staff member who served me.  While taking the cake I realize the icing was drooping off cake. However I thought may be due to traveling that happened. I stored the cake in cool dry place on Saturday evening when we cut the cake and tasted it it was TOTALLY DISAPPOINTING SITUATION , THE CAKE WAS SPOILED, WITH A BAD BUTTER OR OIL TASTE COMING FROM THE CAKE. ALSO THE ICING WAS GIVING TOTALLY SOUR , BITTER TASTE.                                                      ", "\r\n It was evening on Saturday, so I called Klassy Colombo on  Sunday however there was no response.  I called in on Monday and informed Manager ROSHAN is requested me to meet him on Friday, when I come in to the outlet and he will do something about it.  ", "\r\nI went in today 12th  May 2017, This ROSHAN Man is a man who really do not care about customers. He said he can remember me calling him and he say i need the spoil cake to taste to see if its true. My bill average when i walk in to Kalssy Colombo is above LKR1000, he say you may be a customer who comes you should keep the spoil cake and bring it to me. who on earth will store a spoil cake.  This man ROSHAN is a very bad guy who does not know how to talk to customers HE IS THE MOST RUDE, ARROGANT , BIG-HEADED PERSON WHO IS NOT SUITABLE  TO BE A MANAGER . He say he checked with chef and OWNER of Klassy - I can\u2019t imagine if the OWNER IS A SUCH STINGY PERSON. HE SAID OWNER REQUESTED TO SAY THIS HAPPENS EARLIER TOO WITH CUSTOMERS BUT WE CANT HELP IT, WE WILL NOT PROVIDE A COMPENSATION TREAT OR ANY APOLOGY TO ANY CUSTOMERS.   ROSHAN THE SO CALLED MANAGER NEVER EVEN SAID SORRY FOR WHAT HAPPEN EVEN, SAID I CANT HELP IT THESE THINGS HAPPEN EVEN THE OWNER SAID TO IGNORE CUSTOMER COMPLAINS.                                                                 I WILL NEVER RECOMMEND ANY ONE KLASSY COLOMBO AGAIN VERY CHEAP OWNER AND STAFF.", "\r\n\n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    I've also tried their chocolate cakes a couple of years back, and they were divine!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Vegetable Patties and Milk toffees are yum!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    They have a branch in Battaramulla as well (turning right just before the Commercial bank on the main road - coming from the Colombo side). Their ribbon cake is also very good.", "\r\n", "\r\nThey used to have some very satisfying flying saucer shaped toasties in the mornings on certain days (mostly weekends) but seemed to have stopped as of around a year ago.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Their yummy chicken pastry (used to be Rs.80) was our regular treat on the way home from A/L classes! We used to go to classes mainly knowing we'll be dropping into Klassy on the way back!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Best pastries in town. period.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I like their sausage with cheese roll its yummy", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I just LOVE their home make garlic/tomato sauce. Divine\u2026 !!!! Also, their ala toffee (potatoe toffee), milk toffee, sausage and cheese rolls, sausage pastries are a family fav!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Best butter cake period. But try to buy it when its fresh out of the over. The fish pattie is also good. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    No one has pastries taste so good except for them \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    They have the best butter cake and Eclairs \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    They do have a wide range of good pastries and love their home made sauce!! I end up eating more of it every time. The mushroom roll is a must try.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Egg and bacon pastry is yummy!!!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Could you please change the telephone number of Klassy, down De Fonseka Place since the number given on this web page is for Klassy, Battaramulla. - Thank you. Diane", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    tel no is still not changed though they were helpful for information on Thimbirigasyaya\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Have tried the Cholocate Cake\u2026 divine!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    The chocolate cake is amazing! So is their butter cake with chocolate chips :) I would definitely recommend Klassy for any ocassion.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Food is classy\u2026the best\u2026bt the sales girls need a lil bit of descipline\u2026 saw them imitating customers", "\r\n", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    The sales girls are extremely impolite and unhelpful. I don't appreciate being served butter cake with a side of eye-rolling! Honestly, such a buzzkill. ", "\r\nAside from that, the food is top. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    The best is their home made secret garlic and tomato sauce. GOSH. I;ve been eating there since my wee school days :D\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    @T-buns", "\r\nYes I agree. Most times they are sort of frowning or in a bad mood.But at times, they can smile too -but kind of rare\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    The home-made ginger beer is the best in SL!!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    The Klassy Bacon & Egg pastry WAS the best snack one could find in Colombo.  Today it's a Egg pastry and if your lucky to find a bacon end I strongly suggest you buy a lottery ticket asap . Sad but true and hope they don't hoidwink their customers anymore. The eclaies are divine.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    They serve the best Bacon and Egg pastry in Town. but what is said abt the sales  girls are very true. very unfriendly.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I went back, driven by the nostalgic memories of the yummy chicken pie of my AL days. ", "\nThe chicken pie filling tastes like plastic, and the chocolate cupcakes were dry. There's also this unpleasant plasticky smell around the place that's the same as the taste in the chicken pie. ", "\nThis chocolate mousse is too gelatinous, and not creamy enough. Staff attitude is grumpy, didn't even get a smile or a 'you're welcome' when I said 'thank you'. Will definitely not go back or recommend anyone to do so.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Yes the food is great. I love the vegetables Chinese roll and the meringue. However, was disappointed with the attitude of the sales personnel and especially the cashier. I went in around 3.45 pm on a Sunday. They close at 4.00. The first response I got from the girl at the cashier was \"app\". I made my purchase which came to Rs.250.00. I presented a Rs. 1000.00 to which she made a face. Then when I looked at her she said that she had bundled the cash and would have to now unbundle. I paid by card and left wondering why I ever tolerated all that! On the other hand, the security guard was very sweet. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Food is great if the fat is a bit less!", "\nThe cashiers are morose and like the bus conductors - no change syndrome seems to have come here too!", "\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Absolutely! Maybe ex bus conductors!", "\nEvery single time I've been there, they are complaining about change money\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    the worst experience i got from them, they gave me a bread toast which was in black color over toasted one, when i taste that only bitter taste i got it from it. Gave the toast back to them, they kept it and refused to gimme the replacement. Fun part was, when i asked the manager's number they gave a phone number which is completely not responding. worst hospitality\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    WRONG! Phone number. The number is 011 4 252 502 \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Thanks for the heads up! Changed it.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Klassy is no longer on De Fonseka Place. \n                                            "], "contact": "Call 0114 252502", "address": "2B De Fonseka Road, Colombo, Sri Lanka ", "directions": "At the intersection of Dickmans Road (Sir Lester James Peiris) and De Fonseka Road.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["07:00 AM \u2013 07:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 07:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 07:00 PM", "07:00 