                     ", "\n\n                                    The food is good and the kottu is nice (asked them to make it less greasy and they did). They don't accept credit cards so keep cash in hand. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Agree with Karthik.Good kottu in good servings.Their drinks were good too.Not expensive in comparisen to most food places around town.relaxing place.but the washroom hygiene could improve more\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Guys they have hands down the BESt eclairs in the whole world!seriously\u2026I know my eclairs\u2026ive tried it all!but getting your hands on them is another story altogether.they arrive at exactly 11.45am  (with the lunch) and finished withing an hour usually. (I have gone back empty handed many times after driving all the way from rajagiriya\u2026in my defense i was pregnant)\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Ok I've went to this place today. Food is not good. My wife didn't even touch the plate. It's really not good.", "\nBy the way it's sunday and lunch. Can't comment on other days.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Good place to hang-out with a fruit-juice. Can wait for hours, best place to have informal 5-6 guys meetings. On an unrelated note, staff are not much polite with guests (although, the don't mind us occupying the place for hours for a fruit-juice). By any means avoid the tables by the kitchen in the outdoor dine-in area where its too dark in the night, smelling garbage, and the interrupting noise from the kottu bar. If you plan to dine in-door, remember its self-service in the indoor area. And the way they tell you is not at all good.", "\r\nOn average, good place to have an informal meeting for low cost.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    The Staff are really rude. I was there with a friend two days ago and my friend had a laptop. As soon as he opened the flap a waiter came and said ' can't use laptops after 5' we were a bit shocked\u2026then I started checking my iPad and the same guy came and said ' can't use that either' I wanted to speak to a manager, but the manager was the same he very rudely said we don't want ppl to come and use laptops and things without eating anything! We had literally been there for less than 10 mins\u2026.we got so put off\u2026we drove to commons\u2026.really sad cause we love tasty's food. Hope they look into this and rectify this.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Six of us went for dinner last evening at about 6.45pm,  No one paid any attention, then saw a half bald waiter (Name Vicky, found out later) who would have worked for the nazis, looked damn angrily at us  as if we had trespassed his home and left us. Tried to get the attention of another and he pointed to another who in turn poked another and pointed in our direction. Finally a hard  working  harassed chap came to our table and  threw 2 menu cards and disappeared.  After another long wait someone else turns up who happen to be the manager, seems like he just finished his duty at Barney Raymonds and very solemly  stands  stiff without a smile.  We ordered, and then waited and waited, after about half an hour one dish comes, another 15min later the other comes , we were lucky that we got our orders within the next hour so our conversation was great as we could finish eating one at a time.  We left the place as soon as we paid and that was around 9.30pm!! wasted time. The mango milk shake we ordered tasted like some one had washed his hand in Luckspray milk powder and dragged a rotten mango through it. When we complained they changed it and it tasted fine! so they know that a good job can be done! Some  white skins sat at the next table and they were served with cloth napkins, their candles were lit and 2 waiters were hovering around them! In contrast we had to ask for tissues\u2026 will never step in there again even though the ambience is good the service is rotten\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    For a couple years I ate here at least once a week and loved it. The fusion part of the menu was excellent and I loved the clay pot rice dishes. Sadly they no longer serve all of the quality dishes, like the clay pots, and are limited to Sri Lankan comfort food. I no longer recommend it.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Extremely poor service. Very rude staff. Especially the big headed cashier wearing glasses and the other dark tall manager. Probably the WORST SERVICE in town\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    It's true, the staff and management are extremely rude with customers.They dismiss you like you're inconveniencing them and won't even take the time to seat you properly or give menus. Always time-rushed, even with few diners and you can't call on them to save your life. Such a disappointment because the food is quite tasty and real value for money but the negative treatment of customers out-weight whatever the restaurant has working in it's favour. Hope they can rectify this.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Service need some improvements. Is any of the manager in the place reading this thread? They should start to accept the credit cards at least those POS machines pr", "\r\novided by HNB and Sampth \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I've been there only once. Nobody even came to our table to give the menu when we went there. We  had to stand up and look for a waiter and finally found one who passed by. Later i was served a plate of super burnt Mongolian rice. Extremely poor staff service. Dirty place. I will never ever visit again!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I've been back two times since my last post and I have to say that the service has improved a bit. The manager is still anti-social as ever and stares down customers instead of helping them but on both occasions we had a very pleasant and helpful waiter who served us so kudos to him for at least trying. The food has always been delicious, great service could take it to the next level.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Some negative posts describe an entirely different cafe on the 5th to the one some of us know. Usually go there for take away, & the staff there are very polite. Service is quick. The food is really good too, Western menus and short eats, haven't tried kottu.", "\r\n Maybe if you're a pretty female it helps. \u2026\u2026\u2026.just kidding!  \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    EXTREMELY RUDE STAFF. Especially this half bald waiter. I was putting my sandal on and had just lifted by leg up on to the chair to put the straps on, when he shouted from across the place like a school teacher beckoning with his finger saying \"Put THAT down\" with an angry face. Extremely repulsed. Sad to say I WILL NEVER BE GOING THERE AGAIN. Despite the food being good; they need to change their waiters; half witted imbeciles. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Sabeer it is cottect that the manager should shout at you for putting your foot up on the chair. The chair is for customers to sit on, therefore if you put your sandal on it, it's going to leave dirt and germs on the chair which will in turn get on the customer's backside. ", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    are they improved now?\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Not that great with the service, waiters always seem to be scatterbrained and missing in action but their food still remains tasty and value for money. Very popular spot for weekday lunch as it's patronised by a lot of office goers and parents after school, etc. Like I said, go for the food and ambience, service still needs improvement but you have the occasional moment where all three are on point. Also not that expensive compared to similar dining places.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    do they accept credit card because when i went last time they didnt. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    good? err\u2026", "\nIn my experience, the pasta and rice dishes that are usually in that buffet like thing during lunch hours is definitely not enough for two and not all that great, if anything it's loaded with oil.", "\nsome of the short eats are good.", "\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Decent amounts and the prices were quite reasonable. Food was quite tasty.A good value for money spot :)\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I have dined here many times. The food is quite good and the atmosphere is nice but unfortunately the service ruins everything. ", "\nThe wait for the food is way too long even when the restaurant is not crowded. The staff is too aloof to be in the hospitality industry. I hope the owners address these issues soon. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I had a vegi rice today and felt like worst meal I had in 2015. No taste at all except huge amount of chili.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    If you are looking for a place to dine in with a limited budget and good environment, this is the place to go. Thumbs up\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Overpriced\u2026 Fried rice and Nasigoreng is 1000 bucks\u2026 not worth at all\u2026", "\nAvoid the Fried rice with Hotbutter cuttle fish.", "\nThese guys DO NOT know what Hot Butter Cuttlefish IS\u2026.", "\nThey've topped with the cheese sauce that tastes really bad!\n                                            "], "contact": "Call 0112573765", "address": "108 5th Lane, Colombo 3 ", "directions": "Turn off Thurstan Road just past the Thurstan College, going past Flower Drum. From Duplication Road, it's the left turn after the Bellagio Casino.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["06:30 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "06:30 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "06:30 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "06:30 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "06:30 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "06:30 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "06:30 AM \u2013 11:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Sri Lankan", "Mongolian", "Bakery"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 500 - Rs. 1000", "dishes": ["Kottu"], "overall_rating": "2", "quality_rating": "1", "service_rating": "3", "ambience_rating": "4", "near_by_places_names": ["Olive Garden Restaurant", "Flower Drum", "The Kandos Shop ", "The Cake Factory (5th Lane)", "Coffee & Company"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["28, Thurstan Road, Colombo 3", "38, Thurstan Road, Colombo 3", "38/1, Thurstan Road, Colombo 3", "91A, 5th Lane, Colombo 3", "37/3, Pedris Road, Colombo 03"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 100 m away", " 132 m away", " 140 m away", " 145 m away", " 153 m away"], "similar_places": ["Urban Green", "Navro Beach Restaurant"]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/roccos/review-70163", "name": "Rocco's", "excerpt": "Rocco's has a good dine-in restaurant in Rajagiriya serving wood-fired pizza with a wide range of toppings.", "yamu_review": ["Rocco's has a lovely dine-in restaurant on Nawala Road, around the Rajagiriya side, that serves up really good wood-fired pizza, ravioli, lamb chops and tiramisu. They've got quite an expansive menu, with over 30 pizza toppings to choose from, and their staff is fast and attentive, making for a smooth experience overall. They're only open after 5 PM, so we dropped in for dinner.", "You can really go to town with the toppings available at Rocco's, what with an abundance of pork products from bacon to pepperoni to parma ham, marinated lamb to smoked salmon, duck and, yes chicken. Our main gripe, though, was the pricing. A 9\" pizza costs Rs 850 for Margherita and Rs 1300 for Salmone Affumicato (smoked salmon). So, we decided to go half-half and try out at least four toppings.", "Behold, one half five cheese, one half parma ham. The Pizza Amore - Five Cheese (Rs. 600 for half of 9\") was really creamy, with the ricotta coming through nicely. It's a combination of ricotta, blue cheese, parmesan, mozzarella, and, in addition to the usual four, emmental. If you're tired of the same old mozarella, the tangy, creamy (and not oily!) flavours on this are a treat.\u00a0", "The Prosciutto Crudo con Rucola (Rs. 750 for half of 9\") was quite generous, with the piece of parma ham covering the whole slice, and a rocket leaf to each. I really love when a pizza has got fresh ingredients to it, and this one really works because of the rocket leaf. While priced at a hefty Rs. 1850, the 14\" could be compared to the pizzas from Oro 1889. They may not use 00 flour here, but the dough is good enough to hold up the toppings and not take away from those flavours.", "The star of the show, though, was the Salmone Affumicato (Rs.\u00a0650 for half). With some capers, onions and a lovely dill sauce, this one blew us away. The salmon shines bright, with just the right amount of acidity. There aren't too many onions, so those don't get in the way. We highly recommend it.", "The other half on our second pizza was the Gorgonzola e\u00a0Funghi (Rs. 575\u00a0for half) and it was quite disappointing. We couldn't taste the blue cheese, much, which made it out to be just mozzarella and mushroom. Too subtle to make an impression, we wouldn't order this again.", "They've got a few options for drinks, hot and cold, so you can grab a cappuccino or a cafe latte for around Rs 350. We tried the Strawberry Iced Tea (Rs. 250) and it was actually quite good. Served just chilled, the flavour isn't synthetic, it actually tastes like there's strawberry juice in there. You can actually smell it.\u00a0", "I had the lime juice (Rs. 200), because I really like lime juice, and it was good. Not too sweet, but also not particularly tangy. Inoffensive lime juice and inoffensive price.", "We tried the lemon meringue pie (Rs. 400) and it was good. The pastry itself is a bit hard, but the flavours are there. The meringue is nice and fluffy and you get enough of lemon to sate\u00a0your craving. You can check out the desserts in the fridge by the entrance, and pick what looks best. We had a not so smooth experience with the cheesecake, so maybe skip that and try a tiramisu (Rs. 450).", "Since we weren't in our usual neck of the woods, we called in a local, a resident of Rajagiriya, and decided to try the lamb chops (Rs. 1500) that were recommended to us by a friend. This one reminded me of the lamb chop we were served at Grande Gourmet, and it wasn't exceptional, either. They serve it well-done, and you can see that they've put some herbs into the preparation, which adds a bit to the flavour. The mash is alright, just creamy enough, and the sauce that comes with has a smokey flavour to it. It's quite pricey, though, and they have other meat dishes on their menu, but this was the only one we tried. Still not sure whether that's the way to go at Rocco's, if you're a regular diner, please do advise in the comments.", "We also tried the Ravioli & Spinach (Rs. 1,100) which gives you the choice of mushroom or beef. We tried with mushroom and it was pretty good. The pasta itself was al dente, and the alfredo sauce was creamy, as it should be. I personally found the sauce to be a little sweet, and reminiscent of milk powder, but the others disagreed. Three people can share this one, and you get about 6 or 8 pieces.", "Rocco's is a pleasant place to be. There's two ladies at the front office who welcome you if you make eye contact, and their staff seems well-trained and are quite attentive. They've got some space upstairs, too, but we'd recommend making a reservation if you're going with a group. It seems to do well with families, as we saw one happily going at their meal while we were there. The lighting is not very bright but very warm and yellow, with black and white photos of people eating pasta on the walls.\u00a0", "We liked that you see the cooks as soon as you walk in, working on the dough and firing up the pizza. They smile at you when you leave.\u00a0", "While it seems to be best suited for those who live around the area, Rocco's does really good pizza at a steep price. Honestly, the pricing is closer to Oro than any other pizzeria, and we're not sure if we could afford to dine here often. Still, if we do go back, the smoked salmon and the parma ham are the way to go. If you live in Nawala or Rajagiriya and haven't dined here, you definitely should. The 9\" pizza is quite small, with only six slices, so you may\u00a0want want to go with the 14\" half-half. They also do delivery, which we've written about before, but they're better at their dine-in location.", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Best suited for those living around Nawala/Rajagiriya. Really good toppings on wood-fired pizza.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Rocco's in Nugegoda is yet another one of the many pizzerias that has gained popularity for it's delivery. Their wood fire pizzas, while not terrible in any way, just aren't as good as some of our top spots.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    The real problem with local pizzas is the bacon; bacon being something of a loose term in Sri Lanka, used to denote anything ranging from chicken ham to the actual thing. And this was the problem we had with Rocco's - the bacon\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0dbb\u0dc3 \u0dad\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dca\u0da7\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dba\u0db1\u0dc0\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca, \u0dbb\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dca\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0d91\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca. \n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dd3\u0dba \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0db8\u0dd6\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dad\u0db8\u0dba\u0dd2, \u0db6\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca. \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db6\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0da0\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0d85\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dad \u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca. \u0d91\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0da0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd1 \u0db6\u0dda\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0daf\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d85\u0daf\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf. \u0dbb\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0d85\u0db4 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0da7\u0dd4 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0d91\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2. \n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            Tried the tomato soup and marinara pizza. The tomato soup was piping hot when served (the way I like it) and full of tomato chunks. The pizza crust was thin, crunchy and just the right charring with their wood fired oven. They're in the process of renovating the place so do expect some houseflies buzzing around, Wi-Fi issues and lack of condiments (ran out of tobasco). This place will soon be packed with fans craving for tasty Italian food!\n                                    ", "\n                                            made a delivery order. the quality of pizza was really good\u2026 Delivery time quite decent. tiramisu was quite good\u2026 very few plc s in Colombo get it right.\n                                    ", "\n                                            ", "\n                                    ", "\n                                            the pizza was tasteless. the tomato sauce was thin on thinly spread. not fresh, lacking essential spices like oregano. the chicken sausage was underdone. and no one in Colombo can make a decent crust. one that rises at the edge and is crispy on the outside and hollow or airy within. ", "\n\n                                    ", "\n                                            After discovering Rocco's a few months ago, I love this place! The Caprese is one of my favourites, along with the range of pizzas, all of them have been great! During Christmas season they had a Turkey Pizza with a variety of combinations which was amazing and delicious! From the quality of the food to the price, it is definitely worth checking out the place!  \n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    sorry about being the possible cause of leading you astray with your pizza choice. Having checked the menu on Facebook yesterday after a break of a few months, I see a few changes. For one, there's only one ham pizza now and nothing with bacon in the listings.", "\r\n", "\r\nPerhaps they have become a victim of their own success? I have never ordered sides but the quality of pizza has been consistently good in the past.", "\r\n", "\r\nYou are right about the ingredients though. If finding decent bacon is difficult, finding edible pepperoni is very much an impossibility. Roccos passed that test for me when I ordered their pepperoni pizza, so I had high hopes.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Check out : Pasta Hut on Stanley Tillekeratne Mawatha, in Nugegoda.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    its closed now!!!! \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Have been trying Roccos pizza for quite a while and I keep going back. i'm just onto my third loyalty card which speaks for itself. Try the pepperoni and bacon guys and also the meat fest - these two are my favourites.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I hadn't heard of Rocco's before, thanks to you I checked them out!!! I had the Prosciutto, oh man!! The combination of the Rucola was great! Looking forward to checking out  another topping real soon!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    we tried out Rocco's a few weeks back, but it was pretty dissapointing.", "\r\nit took considerable time for them to deliver the pizza so it was not even warm when it arrived + we ordered sea food\u2026and we could literally count the pieces of sea food in the pizza\u2026it was very few.", "\r\nSo we were not happy with the experience at all.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    took ages to deliver and very mediocre pizza for the price with very sparse toppings nothing like wijeya beach for this stuff guys! roccos has sand in their pizza too so their cooking system must not be that great as well\u2026go pro and go harpos if ur craving decent quality pizza - the sri lankans trying to do this Roccos Michelangelos do not know wtf they are doing so dont bother\u2026.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Had this for dinner last night, while the pizza itself was very nice, it's highly over priced. Pizza hut and Dominos do half and half pizzas and they don't charge extra for the two different toppings. It's the one price you pay for the pizza. They really should tell their customers that they charge for each separate topping! Rs.2525 for 2 9inch pizzas (the size of a small personal pan pizza) is very over priced and definitely not worth it! \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    booze options? can you bring your own vino?\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Disappointing!   I called at 7.25pm today\u2026and was told it will take about 45 mins for a delivery. I agreed and specifically told the lady on the phone to ask the rider to call me for directions. I just now got my delivery it's 9.00pm and my pizza is cold. It's over priced and poor service! \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I must agree about the delivery times. They set expectation for 45min but occasionally deliver around 1hr 15m after the call. I suspect the delivery bottleneck is not baking, but actual transport, or waiting for transport. Because the pizza was noticeably cooler than I'd prefer it. They should try a simple queue management system like Pizza Hut or Domino's so that the items comes out the oven only around the time a rider is available to take it. And a single rider shouldn't be doing multiple circuits around Nugegoda with a stack of pizzas bleeding heat. If they're not already using them, they really need to get some of those insulation pouches to carry the pizza in.", "\r\n", "\r\nThat said, the pizza is probably the best available for delivery at that price range.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    The beef ravioli was not good. I found hard pieces of fat in the minced meat and was also not tasty.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Can some one tell me the best vegetable pizza here?  Want to give a try\u2026", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    \"The competition between pizzerias in Colombo has heated up over the past few years with the likes of Santore and Domenico's coming in with very competitive prices\"", "\r\n", "\r\nDomenico's pricing is on par (or just slightly above) the other thin crust wood fired pizzas around\u2026", "\r\n", "\r\nbut you CANNOT call Santore's pricing competitive, it's an expensive pizza. BUT I rate them as the best currently in Colombo. They use authentic ingredients, pork based cured meats, Italian cheeses (the Lankan made substitutes don't offer the same taste & texture; cured artichokes, parma ham, prosciutto, gorgonzola & parmigiono reggiano cheeses for example.", "\r\n", "\r\nI don't know what brand of chorizo Rocco's is using, assuming it's probably chicken chorizo.", "\r\nThe local Cargill's \"black label\" CHICKEN chorizo is the best available  at the supermarkets, but is a poor substitute to the real pork based cured sausage. The Cargills sausage is too dry because there is no pork fat. It's impossible to replicate with chicken fat the same unctuousness that pork fat gives. Also pork fat has a far superior flavour to chicken fat\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Actually since Domenico's came up, Santore's has reduced the price of their pizzas all around and the prices you'll see on the menu are for 13'' pizzas, whereas the prizes quoted here are for 9'' pizzas.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Try their ravioli\u2026. Some great combos of fillings and sauces\u2026. With all of them being delicious!! Also the brushchetta is awesome.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Love the food at Rocco's, there's a lot more options in their dine in menu. Drooling at the thought of the Bacoroni and Diavolo. Rocco's you rock!!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Hi Yamu, I am very interested to note who reviewed the risotto. Risotto is meant to be thick and creamy. And if its a cheese base, then it does give a very cheesy taste. Risotto will take on the texture and thickness of the base, as this is what is absorbed into the grains\u2026also, most gourmets add a dollop of thickening cream at the end, just to give it a bit more texture and thickness. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Having sampled the restaurants of Verona recently (most of which boasted a sri lankan chef,if not two\u2026) we had withdrawal symptoms - so we decided to try somewhere we hadn't - Rocco's - and boy were we pleased! The menu is an extensive and exciting one - and our choices certainly lived up to our expectations -  the Ricotta and Spinach ravioli with pesto sauce is a must and likewise the Capricciosa (ham, artichokes, anchovies, olives, mushrooms and mozarella) - trust me, you won't be disappointed! There's some seriously good cooking going on here and we are already planning what we want to try next. And this gets better - you can also bring your own bottle of plonk. Sorry, forgot to mention the desserts - we ended our meal with tiramisu and cassatta - felt as if i'd almost died and gone to heaven\u2026\u2026 needless to say, Rocco's Rocks! Well done girls\u2026.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I was lucky enough to dine at Rocco's soon after opening and found it to be a very pleasing example of Italian food in Sri Lanka.  I'm from Melbourne, Australia, and when we travelled to Sri Lanka last year I was surprised and excited to see the range on offer at Rocco's.  Last time I visited the island it was Pizza Hut or nothing!!  I had the BBQ Chicken pizza and my husband had the Tropicale.  Both of us were very happy with our meals.  The staff at Rocco's were helpful and polite and the dine-in atmosphere was very enjoyable.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Great pizza, excellent service, quick delivery. Love the bacon and pepperoni, the Diavolo and the anchovy pizzas! \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Can you make reservations at the one on Nawala Road?", "\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Rocco's has only one location. 615A Nawala Rd, Rajagiriya. And sure, give us a call on 072 2012121 to make a reservation.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I tried the Seafood - Shrimp and cuttlefish Pizza and it was not at all great. I've heard much about this place and wanted to give it a try. Yet was unsatisfied with the taste and look of the pizza when it was delivered. The only plus point I noticed is the on-time delivery. I would suggest you all to try out the wood fired pizza at Micheal Angelo's which is situated very closer to this place on Nawala-Koswatta road. (http://www.yamu.lk/place/caffe-michaelangelo/)\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Guys, I think you have done a take-away or delivery review. I have only dined in there a few times and I do have to say, everything there was superb every time we have been there. The waiters were very attentive and the serve was lighting fast ( My father, who is bit impatient when it comes to ordering time was also impressed and commented on that matter). and the pizzas were gorgeous and made with quality ingredients. By the way - you should try the sides - especially the Garlic Bread.  The deserts can be improved, but not bad in any way.", "\nI honestly think that if you do get a chance - do a dine-in review. Honestly, some of the best pizzas  have had - mind you, I have been to a number of Italian pizza joints abroad as well.", "\nAnd comparatively, the food is about 15%-20% cheaper.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    We love the ambiance, the food they have to offer. The pizza is great no two words. We keep going back for the delicious pizza\u2026\u2026 \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Tried Biancaneve 9\" pizza.(For Rs:750 + S.C. Rs:75) Can't satisfied. But customer service was excellent.\n                                            "], "contact": "Call 0722012121", "address": "615A Nawala Road, Rajagiriya ", "directions": "From the Battaramulla Road, turn right onto Nawala Road before the Rajagiriya Children's Park.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["05:00 PM \u2013 10:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 10:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 10:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 10:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 10:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 10:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 10:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Italian"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 1000 - Rs. 1500", "dishes": ["Pizza"], "overall_rating": "4", "quality_rating": "4", "service_rating": "4", "ambience_rating": "4", "near_by_places_names": ["Candy Cakes", "Carino Ice Cream", "Dolce Italia (Rajagiriya)", "Cafe Michaelangelo", "Foster & Reed"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["23, Rajagiriya Gardens, Nawala Road, Rajagiriya (Delivery) ", "30-A Welikadawatte Road, (Off Nawala Rd.) Rajagiriya", "623 Nawala Road, Rajagiriya", "530 Nawala Road, Nawala", "329 & 331/C Nawala Road"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 71 m away", " 111 m away", " 163 m away", " 252 m away", " 422 m away"], "similar_places": ["Domenico's", "Santor\u00e9 Bistro Italiano"]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/leesh/review-188540", "name": "LeeSH", "excerpt": "A charming little sandwich bar owned by the loveliest couple with delicious food.", "yamu_review": ["If you live in Nugegoda or go for tuition classes at Sasip you will definitely know LeeSH. It's a crowd favourite among the tuition kids. This quaint little shop has been around for a long time and since our last review, we were happy to see that their quality and standards have not wavered.", "They have all your popular comfort foods like burgers, sandwiches, submarines, hot-dogs, what have you.\u00a0", "We started off with a Veggie Sub (Rs. 400). It was delicious with an enormous amount of thinly sliced cabbages, carrots, onions, tomatoes and lettuce on top of a small soy patty, with a fried egg topped with a slice of cheese and a drizzle of mayo. The veggies are fresh and crunchy with no\u00a0additives so you can taste all the natural flavours.\u00a0This is actually an ideal portion because I didn't find myself getting full nor was I looking around for more food.\u00a0", "We also tried their Chicken and Cheese Burger (Rs. 300). We would have preferred a bigger patty for that price, but all the same, the patty was juicy and tender with a nice meaty flavour topped with a handful of crunchy veggies and a cheese slice.\u00a0", "We also got a Tuna Burger (Rs. 300) which was our favourite. The tuna paste was homemade with a soft and mushy texture. It was well balanced in terms of flavour and included\u00a0lots of cabbage, tomato and lettuce.\u00a0", "The Brownie and Ice Cream (Rs. 200)\u00a0was top notch. It was served warm with Highland vanilla ice cream. The texture was soft and gooey with a layer of chocolate sauce on top. It wasn't too sweet either but I felt like it was a tad overbaked at the bottom. All in all, it was yum! Enough that we asked for some to takeaway.", "I really wanted to try their iced coffee because that's one of their most popular drinks but unfortunately, it wasn't available. So we opted for a Hot Chocolate.", "The Hot Chocolate (Rs. 300) was by no means\u00a0as good as our favourite at ", " but it was pretty decent. The thick chocolatey texture and the cocoa flavour were strong enough, and we didn't get a sugar rush from drinking it.", "The service especially is something we want to mention here. The place is manned by this lovely couple who genuinely seem to care about that their customers' well being and always make sure that what they serve is clean, fresh and delicious. They are incredibly friendly and always have a smile on their face which is very refreshing to see.", "Our food arrived at a reasonable time so no complaints there. The kitchen is the first thing you meet as you enter and you can see how all your food has been made. They also use eco-friendly brown paper bags for takeaway.", "The place is similar to what you would get on Pinterest if you type \"green decor\" with different shades of green complimenting each other. If you're a clean freak like me, the first thing you would notice is how clean the place is. The beautiful wall art and the wooden furniture gives the place a boutique vibe.\u00a0", "One thing I've always found irksome about the place is their operational hours. It is really confusing so be sure to check the timings we have put up here before you go or just call and check. It would be better if they could stick to consistent hours throughout the week.", "We\u00a0recommend this place if you want to enjoy some comfort food in a peaceful environment. You can even place your order beforehand and pick it up.\u00a0Their prices have gone up since our last visit (4 years ago) but it's not unreasonably high and they do give you your money's worth.", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    A great spot for some delicious burgers in Nugegoda. \n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Exploring the streets of Nugegoda in search of good food, we stumbled upon a charming little sandwich bar, Leesh.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0dbd\u0dd3\u0dc1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd4\u0d9c\u0dda\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0da9 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dda \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8 \u0d9c\u0ddc\u0da9 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d95\u0db1\u0dda \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca. \n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0dbd\u0dd3\u0dc2\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0d9a\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db8 \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbd\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dbd\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0dda\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0d87\u0daf\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0db1\u0dd4\u0d9c\u0dda\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0da9 \u0db1\u0d9c\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd3\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3 \u0d9a\u0dd1\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dba\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dba\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0db4\u0da7 \u0dbd\u0dd3\u0dc2\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0d82\u0da0\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da9\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da0\u0dca \u0db6\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dcf. \u0db4\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dd9 \u0dad\u0db8\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dda\u0d9a \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0d85\u0db4\u0dda \u0d85\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dad\u0db8 \u0db6\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0da9\u0dda, \u0d92 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db6\u0ddd \u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dc0\u0dab\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7\u0db8 \u0d89\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dc4 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dda. \u0db8\u0dda \u0d85\u0db4\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0d82\u0da0\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0db8\u0db1\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf. \u0d92 \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dda\u0db8 \u0d92\u0d9a \u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2. \u0d92\u0d9a \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0d94\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd2 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3\u0db8 \u0da2\u0ddc\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0. \u0d91\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0d9a  \u0da2\u0dd3\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0d85\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dda \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5 \u0db8\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dda. \u0d94\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0d91\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca \u0d87\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2.\n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            ", "\n                                    ", "\n                                            ", "\n                                    ", "\n                                            Lovely place. I had the chicken teriyaki burger and an ice coffee. The burger was simply out of this world. The chicken was grilled to perfection and the right amount of sauces held the burger together. The bread was soft and warm, unlike other sandwich places where the bread is almost cardboard-like. ", "\r\nThe place is so clean and the place is well-kept. The owner's are very sweet and obliging. ", "\r\nI definitely recommend it if you're in Nugegoda and you're looking for a bite. \n                                    ", "\n                                            I go to this shop at least once a week because my school is near this shop! They food is pretty awesome, clean and tasty. The place is cool and fresh and a very nice place to just relax and grab a bite! The owners are really sweet and have a smile all the time! Hate the fact that it's closed most of the times now!!\n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    awww come on guys, where's my veggie icon? yes/no/maybe??? :D \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Of course they are the sweetest couple you'll ever meet. I used to be a regular customer of them when I was living around there starting from the very beginning. Yeap foods are great \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    do they have delivery ? \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Is that location on the map correct?\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    It wasn't, but we've just changed it. Sorry about that!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I just went there for lunch after seeing this on my FB feed. Awesome joint, awesome food, great couple. I've even told them I'll put a comment here. My office is near Nugegoda. There is nothing much here, so glad to see this. If they maintain this level, I'll be a regular customer.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    halaal?\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    <<<<<<<< NOTICE >>>>>>>>", "\r\n", "\r\n May 11th Saturday 2013 LeeSH will Be CLOSED !!!!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Try their Chef's Salad\u2026 I'm a huge salad fan & a salad would be the first thing i try-out when finding a newby\u2026 and i tell you, that was the most awsome, yummiest salad i've tasted so far. It was simply a heaven-on-a-plate when it comes to salad-land!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    It's the freshest food you can eat in town. Plus your money's worth. ", "\r\n The place is Air conditioned and very clean. ", "\r\n Has WIFI\u2026 Yesssss\u2026", "\r\n", "\r\n Well in my point of view everyone should come to this place it's nice and calm place to be plus it's relaxing cos the theme is green colour. ", "\r\n Very friendly couple who run this place is really give you a good service plus they are also really kind and sweet people also you can really enjoy your food.", "\r\n This is like home away from home for me.", "\r\n", "\r\n Hope everyone comes here and also from what you have read so far I hope I gave a clear idea about this place. ", "\r\n", "\r\n With Best Regards", "\r\n Sahan\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Thank you so much for the lovely reviews and feedback.", "\r\n We are so Delighted that your experience with us@ LeeSH was so positive.", "\r\n Thank you for your visit and hope we see you again soon !!!", "\r\n                                   **** ****\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Do you serve halal foods? \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Yes We Do ! :) ", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Thumbs up to Leesh. I heartily recommend it to anyone looking for a good sandwich in Nugegoda. I was amazed at how clean and sparkling the place was and the pleasant atmosphere and service. This combined with the prices make it a winner.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Love their food. One of thr best places \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    If you can find parking, yes a lovely place to eat and do some grocery shopping at the same time.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    @Buwa, Take your extremism and filthy language somewhere else\u2026\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Is this joint closed now?? went there several days & it was closed\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I do Leesh runs often and they are top notch all the time!!! :)\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Very good place. I live close by and patronize this place. They have a really good chicken teriyaki burger. Very good. Only negative is they don't have any pork dishes.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Dear LeeSH Owners (\"THE Sweet Couple!!) . Pl comment on \"it's closed most of the time\u2026\" and ", "\r\n\"\u2026.negative is they don't have any pork dishes\u2026.\"", "\r\nRavi", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Food is fresh, worth for the money you pay.And I happen to love the homely ambiance. Keep it up guys!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Yummy sandwiches and value for money. I had chicken teriyaki burger and he toasted chicken sandwich was grilled to perfection. Brown bread sandwich was very good. All in all, we give it a rating of 8/10\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    We visited this place today and to be honest their food is worth for money. Custom care is also awesome. Nice,  clean place\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Grate Food . Nice couple Very friendly . All of you people should try this place  :) \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Ideal place to hangout!Great service!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Awesome Food. Wish they have more parking space\u2026\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    As of May, 2016 how is this place? Is Leesh still maintaining the standards it was known for?\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Went there recently. Very friendly customer service. Opted for combo 1 and true their burgers are delicious. I couldn't even finish it because it is filled with lot of cheese n meat. I will give 5 stars for rating.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    It was, It is and It will be the best Sandwich Bar in SL\u2026 Will visit again, again, again and again\u2026 \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    excellant place for a quick snack and worth the price of their sandwiches and burgers.Good vustomer service by the couple as well and loved their hot tea.They continue to maintain the standerds\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Good to know they are still going strong. Not been that way in many moons, but I have been there several times and definitely recommend it.\n                                            "], "contact": "Call 0112823019/0773251736", "address": "245, High Level Road, Jambugasmulla, Nugegoda ", "directions": "Just opposite Bo Sevana on Jambugasmulla Road.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["08:30 AM \u2013 02:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 08:30 PM", "08:30 AM \u2013 02:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 08:30 PM", "08:30 AM \u2013 02:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 08:30 PM", "08:30 AM \u2013 02:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 08:30 PM", "08:30 AM \u2013 02:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 08:30 PM", "08:30 AM \u2013 02:00 PM", "05:00 PM \u2013 08:30 PM"], "cuisine": ["Western"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 500 - Rs. 1000", "dishes": ["Burgers"], "overall_rating": "4", "quality_rating": "4", "service_rating": "4", "ambience_rating": "4", "near_by_places_names": ["Bo Sevana ", "Nils Store", "My Burger", "Ambul Thiyal", "Premadasa Riding School"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["High Level Road, Nugegoda", "No. 261, High Level Road, Nugegoda.", "No. 244, High Level Road, Nugegoda", "295, High Level Road, Nugegoda", "11/12 Melder Place, Nugegoda"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 35 m away", " 53 m away", " 95 m away", " 171 m away", " 196 m away"], "similar_places": ["E-Cafe", "Nine 11 Restuarant & Coffee Shop"]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/peppers-majestic-city/review-15779", "name": "Peppers (Majestic City)", "excerpt": "Over the weekend I found myself wandering about Majestic City doing a bit of shopping. After a couple of tiresome hours of trying to find a gift, I hungrily dragged myself to the spacious, although somewhat crowded, Majestic City food court. They offer a good variety of food to choose from; there\u2019s a Pizza Hut, KFC, Magic Corn, Juice by Roots, Chinese and Mongolian food stalls, and there\u2019s even a small pastry shop in the corner. Personally though, the main feature would have to be Peppers \u2013 Pizza and Pasta.\r\n", "yamu_review": [], "user_reviews": [], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    Com'oooon!! Please!! U call this pizza? Its misleading!! Its NOT pizza, its a pita bread painted with an artificial sweet red sauce and lil shreds of chicken. If ur hungry at MC U can do better with 150 bucks for ur hunger. Like the shop where chariot used to be on the ground floor (opposite com bank ATM), don't know its name, they serve hearty wraps, sams sausages, hot dogs and stuff. They have a big serving of ice cream cones for just 50 bucks. Thats the place for a quick snack. Also there are foot-long burger stall on the basement floor which is decent, tho Im not a fan of boiled-ungrilled sausages.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Agree. Peppers is pretty bad. They do that local thing where the tomato sauce is sickly sweet on the pizza-gross.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    ^ totally agree with HitActionCop, if you are going to try Peppers you r wasting your money \u2026 and that Shop,opposite com bank ATM ( I also can not remember the name) serves yummy Milk shakes too,\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Peppers has been there for as long as I remember\u2026 and while not stellar food, I've rather enjoyed their pasta and pizza. Satisfying as well as value for money!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Try Cheese pasta. Its cheap as well as tasty.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    They roll out a fabulous Hawaiian Pizza\u2026one of the best I've tasted to date\u2026.perfect for the Sri Lankan palate\u2026", "\r\n", "\r\n", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    if you are looking for a wallet friendly quick bite this is the place at MC\u2026\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    These guys been there for ages and it is the best joint to grab something proper\u2026 pasta it is. Pizza is still good.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I've been patronizing them from day one of MC food court and they simply are the best value for mouthful (especially 10 or more years back, but probably holds true still) at the place. I've had their spicy chicken macaroni for 60/- or so those days and while it was no where close to a perfect pasta dish, it was wholly satisfying if you wanted some grub.", "\r\nAgain, not a place where you'd go for gourmet delicacies, but simple, tasty hunger busters.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Totally agree with the review\u2026 MC food court is a place you'd dine in if you are either starving or just about gots no other place to go! However, from all the restaurants there my personal favorite is Peppers not cuz of the pizza (cuz I'm not a pizza fan in general) but the yummy pasta! Guess it depends on your palette but that pasta is well worth the 220-230 bucks you pay.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Super Pizza since i was a kid\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Love their Pizza! :) \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Believe it or not, the pizza here is quite good. They have a unique sweet sauce which makes it their signature flavor. this place has good potential if they plan to expand around the city. I'd recommend anyone eating here. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Agree with hotactionCop! The pizza is horrid. It's almost like they use cheap sweetened tomato sauce from a bottle for the topping, the cheese is not really mozzarella, (but I'll let them have that cos it's very cheap. but it doesn't stretch), sometimes it's cold, and they top it with really dry tasteless chicken. I'd call it flat bread with sweetened bottled tomato sauce, cheese substitute and chicken left overs. :) but hey for Rs. 150 what more can you ask for right? \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    not that great, it's cheap. that's all\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I would always love their Rice with Sausages. love the huge amount of mayonnaise over the salad.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Had quick lunches from there so many times and for the price you can't ask for better. Peppers don't have the best food. But if you are hungry and under a budget it would do. And I think the place HotActionCop is referring to is a cargills thing.", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    love the rice and pasta\u2026 though i don't go there at all, its been my favorite place when i was a kid running around MC :D \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Oh come on! Cussing peppers for not being a proper pizza joint is like cussing your mother when she tries to make her version of KFC or something. Its been that shop in the corner for as long as I remember and giving school kids and \"empty pocket\" boys and girls a happily decent meal. They don't pretend. Its like Green Cabin, its not the best, but when you long for that particular taste, there is only one place to go to. ", "\r\nSo all you haters, there are enough and more places for you to get your perfect pretentious pizza! Leave good ol peppers alone\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    This pizza is really  good .Good tasty .No wonder It's  better than pizza hut pizza . perfect \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Been eating this literally since they opened. Always liked that they haven't changed in over 20 years. Even the staff! The pizza is feel good food and so is the pasta. It has a home-made style to it by a local's standards anyways. It's not meant to be pizza the Italian way. For the nay sayers: Point taken - it's not luxury dining that you obviously expect in a food court (sarcasm) - head to the spot at Liberty Arcade 2nd floor ^^ instead of taking it out on the little guy that kept his business going for all of 19+ years?\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Love this place ! ", "\r\nIts like tradition ! Movie ! then Peppers Pizza ! and none of my friends dares to break the tradition ! I'm a complete sucker for the Hawaiian Pizza :D \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Today i went to pepers @ MC\u2026 thye were kindly invite me to by some thing\u2026 one i pay money for my meal they treat really bad\u2026 this not the way they should talk to customer\u2026 bold guy in the cashier his is like a thug level treat me very bad way in front of my wife\u2026 and thepublic\u2026 he teaching me how to have meal in pepers\u2026 peper top management has to appolagise for this\u2026\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    food quality has dropped. affordable prices. bunch of flies inside the display cabinet sitting on pizza pieces. \n                                            "], "contact": "Call 0114513593", "address": "Galle Road, Colombo, Sri Lanka ", "directions": "\n                ", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["09:00 AM \u2013 09:00 PM", "09:00 AM \u2013 09:00 PM", "09:00 AM \u2013 09:00 PM", "09:00 AM \u2013 09:00 PM", "09:00 AM \u2013 09:00 PM", "09:00 AM \u2013 09:00 PM", "09:00 AM \u2013 09:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Between Rs. 200 - Rs. 500"], "price_range": "Pasta", "dishes": ["American", "Fast Food"], "overall_rating": "3", "quality_rating": "3", "service_rating": "3", "ambience_rating": "1", "near_by_places_names": ["P. G. Martin Wonderworld (Majestic City)", "Luv Esence", "Larich Foods", "KFC - Majestic City", "Mlesna Tea Centre"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["Majestic City, Galle Road, Bambalapitiya, Colombo 4", "No 1, Second Floor, Majestic City, Bambalapitiya", "Level 3, Majestic City", "Galle Road, Bambalapitiya, Colombo 4", "4 Majestic City, Colombo 4"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 7 m away", " 7 m away", " 8 m away", " 11 m away", " 11 m away"], "similar_places": ["Capital City Food Court (Badulla)", "Dinemore (Marine Drive) "]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/hotel-top-form/review-15037", "name": "Hotel Top Form", "excerpt": "Hotel Top Form is an Indian restaurant under the Nugegoda flyover. It's OK, the lunch packets are not especially good but we hear good things about the tandoori.", "yamu_review": ["\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Hotel Top Form is an Indian restaurant under the Nugegoda flyover. It's OK, the lunch packets are not especially good but we hear good things about the tandoori.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0da7\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0da7\u0ddc\u0db4\u0dca \u0dc6\u0ddd\u0db8\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd4\u0d9c\u0dda\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0da9 \u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db8 \u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca. \u0d91\u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3\u0dba\u0dd2. \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd  \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd2\u200d\u0dc1\u0dda\u0dc2 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc4\u0dd0. \u0d92\u0dad\u0dca, \u0d85\u0db4\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0dad\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3\u0dba\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd\u0dcf. \n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            ", "\n                                    ", "\n                                            Try their chicken 65 it is the tastiest! \n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    Try their butter naan with chicken tikka masala\u2026 simply delicious \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    What shehzter said. simply delicious!\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I've patronized them for nearly 20 years now I think (from when I was wee). Butter naan with tikka or butter chicken is kinda their winning dish - simple fare that is tasty and fulfilling. Probably nothing to write home about but if the purpose of food is to taste good and be fulfilling, then those dishes does the job.", "\r\nNowadays, I don't get to visit them too often as parking there is a bit of an issue but as far as I can tell the taste and the quality (from what is was, mind) has not changed from the '90's.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    great fan of their basmati biriyani for more than 15 years!! quality and the taste is still the same.  highly recommend for their butter nan and tikka\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Don't get their fried rice. It just crap. I got a drumstick and there's nothing to eat except to eat the bone. Seems they have got it from an sick chicken. Even the rice is not good. I didn't complaint but thought never go there again.  It cost 260 and for that price there are plenty of places where you can buy good stuff.\n                                            "], "contact": "Call 112812704", "address": "150E High Level Road, Nugegoda ", "directions": "Take the High Level Road out of Colombo, it's just under the flyover, on the right side. You can't turn down there but sometimes you can park under.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Indian", "Sri Lankan"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 200 - Rs. 500", "dishes": ["Biriyani", "Tandoori"], "overall_rating": "2", "quality_rating": "2", "service_rating": "2", "ambience_rating": "2", "near_by_places_names": ["Domino's (Nugegoda)", "Devon Bakeaway (Nugegoda)", "McDonald's (Nugegoda)", "Volsquare", "Mallika Hemachandra Jewellers"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["161 High Level Rd, Nugegoda", "Highlevel Road, Nugegoda, Sri Lanka", "1 Raymond Road, Nugegoda", "159, S De S. Jayasinghe Mawatha, Nugegoda\r\n\r\n", "153, S De S. Jayasinghe Mawatha, Nugegoda"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 36 m away", " 77 m away", " 78 m away", " 95 m away", " 149 m away"], "similar_places": ["Thulasi Hotel (Badulla)", "Dinemore (Kandy)"]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/spicy-cabin/review-17135", "name": "Spicy Cabin", "excerpt": "We heard good things about Spicy Cabin, but our experience simply wasn't that good.", "yamu_review": ["\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    We heard good things about Spicy Cabin, but our experience simply wasn't that good.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0dc3\u0dca\u0db4\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db1\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca\u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7-\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dda \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0da9\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dd2. \u0db6\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddd \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0d94\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dad\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dc5\u0dad\u0dca \u0d85\u0db4\u0dd2 \u0d91\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d86\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba \u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0d91\u0dad\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3 \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2, \u0d91\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dda\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dc0 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0d91\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db6\u0dc0 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dba. \u0da0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dd0\u