{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/which-way-west/review-106775", "name": "Which Way West", "excerpt": "Which Way West is a new pub that serves up okay food.", "yamu_review": ["Which Way West is a new entry into Colombo's pub scene. They're pretty well stocked when it comes to booze and their ladies night offers free cocktails. Food-wise they're alright, finally moving away from the Poppy Hana menu to realize their own. We dropped in for dinner.", "When I first checked out Which Way West, I was disappointed to see that it was still the same old Poppy Hana scene with a different name. This time, though, they've got it together and it's quite clear that it's a new menu. You can go for the peri peri chicken, steak, cuttlefish or a burger. We started off with their Hot Butter Cuttlefish (Rs 595).", "They don't use any\u00a0batter here, so it's not crispy. I'm personally not a fan of this. The flavour is good, but if the crunch is what you're after, this is not for you.", "For mains, we tried the\u00a0Classic Cheese Burger (Rs 645) which\u00a0came with a beef patty and french fries. This was pretty mediocre. The patty wasn't particularly juicy or flavourful, and there was nothing remarkable about the whole thing. At the price, it's not worth it.", "\r\n", "We also tried the Rib Eye Steak (Rs 980). They didn't have imported beef, so we went with the local one, which is much cheaper. The cut is really thin, though, but they did heed our request for it to be prepared medium-rare which is rare. The beef was juicy and cooked just right, so no complaints there. Just wish it was a thicker cut to be considered a steak.", "For dessert, we tried the\u00a0Oreo Ice Cream (Rs 425). This came topped with whipped cream and an Oreo. It's quite yum, actually, and as someone who doesn't enjoy ice cream too much, I quite liked it.", "Service at Which Way West is pretty prompt. They will welcome you as you step in, which is always nice.\u00a0", "You have a few options when it comes to the actual setting. There's an outdoor area, if you want to indulge in some shisha. Then there's the pub area that's dimly lit, with a red glow. Then there's this cafe type scene which is better lit.", "Which Way West is figuring out its own identity, after being weaned off its predecessor. They've got an Acoustic Night where you can win a free appetiser by performing a song with the house band. They've also got a crazy ladies night deal. We noticed a young and hip crowd in the outdoor section when we visited, so maybe this place will catch on. The food can improve, but there's plenty of booze to keep you busy, anyway.", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Which Way West is a new entry into Colombo's pub scene. The food can improve, but there's plenty of booze to keep you busy, anyway.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Serving up sushi and shisha, Which Way West isn't quite as Western as we expected.\n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            Which Way West is generally the first place to go for pre drinks or just a casual beer for the majority of people just out of school or the underage daredevils, it could be a club or it could be a bar and the prices are reasonable. Food is good on the days the chef feels like it. Also it serves both a ladies night and a gents night( discounted or free stuff) And entrance fee can be used to subsidize your bill at the bar. Tends to get overcrowded though. \n                                    ", "\n                                            Their  Oreo Ice-cream is yummylicious!! I like this place. \n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    who the hell are you to take photos of the customers. it looks like you just took it with your phone zoomed in. did you even ask for permission.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I have been curious if you're staff asks permission when taking pictures of other people when doing a review/article.  well David cleared that out for me.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Thanks for the feedback, David. We do generally try and avoid taking photos of people unless it's integral to the article. It's been fixed.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    So it's a pub\u2026 But no review of any drinks? \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    That is probably because Kinita didn't do the review .\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    very confuse\u2026what you wrote is very confusing. Also, where is the customer photo which @ david was upset about? \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    This place is awesome! They have a great lunch buffet with a variety of items (soup, rice, pizza, sushi, dessert) for 1000 bucks. Their a la carte is great too! Had no idea it was meant to be a british pub, but I'm really satisfied with their service, food, shakes and wine so far.  Tip: Try their bubble tea.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Any idea what the alcohol prices are like ? ", "\r\nBeer pitchers/towers in particular. ", "\r\nAlso since its a pub do they have a large screen (Or any screen for that matter) with the main sports channels? \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Just gonna leave my Facebook review here:", "\r\n", "\r\nI don't know which was worse, the sad attempt on a plate that they tried to pass off as food or the deranged greasy haired pretend manager dude who happily made a scene and accused us of not paying our 2000 rupee bill. ", "\r\n", "\r\nWe were even treated to some Bouncer action. Bouncers to protect him from 2 girls with shopping bags -- don't blame him though, I was feeling pretty murderous after being subjected to that godawful hot butter cuttlefish (nothing hot or butter or cuttlefish about it) and there *were* butter knives around -- until our greasy haired friend realised that leaving the bill behind in the bill holder *does not in fact mean* the bill wasn't paid \u2026So folks, to save you from being ambushed by this weirdo and his band of merry men -- for the love of God JUST TAKE THE BILL WITH YOU. Or better yet -- don't go there. Save your tummy *and* eyes from rolling.", "\r\n\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    One of the worst pub I've been to. To start with this place is full of bouncers with no respect. ", "\r\n", "\r\nSecond food wasn't tasty at all. They were below average. Thridly and most importantly they demanded that we have to settle the bill \"every hour\" since most of the people leave the premises without setting the bill and it's apparently their policy! What kind of bullshit is that ? Very disappointed with the expeeeince. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    They don't have the Japanese food apparently.  \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Japanese food is not served at WWW that's poppy Hana and its closed and opened at Urban Kitchen:) ", "\r\n\n                       