{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/karapincha/review-185009", "name": "Karapincha", "excerpt": "A great spot for authentic Sri Lankan cuisine.", "yamu_review": ["Karapincha is\u00a0on Galle Road, adjoining the Concord Grand Hotel. It has a huge green sign on top, so you won't miss it.\u00a0", "The menu is pretty interesting, with a wide range of authentic Sri Lankan cuisine to choose from, and relatively reasonable prices.", "We got a portion of ", " (Tempered Yellow\u00a0Rice - Rs. 200), ", " (Tempered Cashew cooked in Coconut Milk - Rs. 429) and the Chef's special ", "\u00a0(Chicken Black Curry with Fried Rice - Rs. 523) and a ", " (Egg Salad - Rs. 132).", "The\u00a0rice portions were cooked perfectly with strong spices like karapincha\u00a0(of course), cinnamon and cloves to bring out that perfect rice aroma. I can't tell you enough how much I\u00a0love a good cashew curry and this was oh so delicious! The gravy was so creamy and the cashews were soft and easy to bite into.", "The chicken was nothing special but slightly on the\u00a0pricier side for a small portion but the gravy was seasoned well and full of flavour. It was just the right amount of spiciness we were looking for.\u00a0The egg salad was a great addition with fresh veggies and boiled eggs.", "For dessert, we got a Cream Caramel (Rs. 200). While the presentation was a bit unpleasant,\u00a0the texture was everything you would want in a caramel pudding; soft and creamy with the typical sweet and milky flavour.", "We tried a Watermelon Juice (Rs. 209) and a Hot Ginger\u00a0Tea (Rs. 110) which were both superb. The watermelon thankfully had very little sugar in addition to its natural sweetness. The tea was surprisingly good and had a slight ginger flavour. It was a proper homemade tea that you could have without sugar and\u00a0would still taste good.\u00a0", "Service was quick. Our food arrived within 10-15 minutes. The staff was friendly and courteous which is always refreshing to see.\u00a0", "They have done a decent job in terms of design but it could be improved. Nevertheless, there\u00a0was ample space for large or small groups amidst wooden tables and\u00a0chairs with nicely colour coordinated\u00a0cutlery and tableware.\u00a0", "It was a quality experience. The food was delicious and tasted homemade with very little additives. Our total bill came to around Rs. 2400 including service charges and taxes which was very reasonable considering the flavour, texture and the portion sizes.\u00a0", "We highly recommend you try this place. It's", " as well cause they prepare your food pretty fast.\u00a0", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Delicious and authentic Sri Lankan food.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0d85\u0db4\u0dda \u0d94\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0da2\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dc3\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dad\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d95\u0db1\u0dda \u0db1\u0db8\u0dca, \u0d94\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca. \n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            One of the best places in town to experience authentic Sri Lankan cuisine at a reasonable price.\n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    Wow !! let us also try this out soon. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    The food was fresh, properly prepared and a great value for the price. i  highly recommend it.\n                                            "], "contact": "Call 077 274 4788", "address": "141 Galle Road, Dehiwela, Sri Lanka ", "directions": "Adjoining Concord Grand Hotel.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Sri Lankan"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 1000 - Rs. 1500", "dishes": ["Rice And Curry"], "overall_rating": "5", "quality_rating": "5", "service_rating": "5", "ambience_rating": "4", "near_by_places_names": ["Kushmi Foods", "Pizza Hut", "Kebabish ", "The Chariot (Dehiwala)", "Habitat for Humanity"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["107, Galle Road, Dehiwala. ", "No.101 Galle Road,\nDehiwela.", "91, Galle Road, Dehiwala", "86 Galle Road, Dehiwala", "22/5, Station Road, 10350 Dehiwela, Sri Lanka"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 159 m away", " 164 m away", " 288 m away", " 372 m away", " 388 m away"], "similar_places": ["River View Restaurant", "Sanekvin Restaurant & Bar"]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/food-waves/review-179830", "name": "Thiru Murugan's Food Waves", "excerpt": "An Indian vegetarian restaurant with an extensive menu of North and South Indian cuisine.", "yamu_review": ["Food Waves is not the most crowded place but it has been running\u00a0for years. It's a vegetarian restaurant serving both North and South Indian cuisine. While some aspects of the\u00a0food were alright, the service was extremely disappointing.", "The food arrived pretty quick, which isn't saying much because there were only about three more customers\u00a0aside from us. We got the Moghalai Biriyani (Rs. 350) and a side of Paneer Butter Masala (Rs. 400). The subtle use of spices in the biriyani and the well-cooked basmati rice mixed with a handsome amount of cashews were great, but the amount of oil could not be overlooked. We also missed the boiled egg that normally comes with the dish, and\u00a0the\u00a0portion was really small and not worth the price. \u00a0", "The\u00a0Paneer Butter Masala is one of their most popular dishes. Although it tasted more like tofu than paneer, it was succulent in its own way and the gravy did wonders. It went very well with the biriyani and the rest of the dishes we ordered and was the only dish that wasn't dripping with oil.\u00a0", "Their naan and kulcha weren't available for lunch so we settled for a Butter Parotta (Rs. 300). You get two parottas with a side of sambar and a coconut chutney. The parottas were really tasty - crispy around the edges and soft in the middle. The coconut chutney worked well with the parotta but the sambar was watery with no texture or flavour.\u00a0", "We also ordered the Cheese Parotta (Rs. 380) which was a huge disappointment. When it said cheese we were expecting cheese\u00a0", "the parotta, not\u00a0a sloppy smattering of grated cheese. It's not worth the extra bucks.\u00a0", "They didn't have any of the Lassis we wanted to try out, so we settled for two Lime Juices (Rs. 180 each) and a Lemon Soda (Rs. 220). I know you can't tell the difference, neither could we. There wasn't enough lemon or lime in both. The\u00a0texture and flavour weren't strong enough either. They both tasted, more or less the same, and the only thing it did was help wash out all that oil.\u00a0", "The place seemed congested with so many tables and chairs\u00a0which I don't think they need considering most people just come there for takeaway. The furnishing, however, was quite fancy.\u00a0", "In terms of service, it didn't come off as a surprise to us when the service was just downright rude and inconsiderate. There have been so many complaints about their service in other reviews going back years and they clearly couldn't care less about it. The waiter was telling us what was available as he was walking away. I don't see what his hurry was, seeing as the place was practically deserted.", "It was rather a disappointing experience. They do seem to have a clear customer base, particularly for takeaway orders, but we wouldn't count ourselves among them. Their parottas are alright if you're willing to look past the oil, but we couldn't.\u00a0"], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            ", "\n                                    ", "\n                                            Very bad\n                                    ", "\n                                            One of da worst restuarant tht i hav been  because of poor service i dnt recommend anyone to go thr\ud83d\ude23\ud83d\ude11\ud83d\ude25\n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    Very accurate review. Very spacious restaurant, parking available. Service is speedy, menu/options vast. But quality of food is average, and at times below average. ", "\r\n", "\r\nHaving been there twice i ve decided i am not going again. Instead i go for Thaalis in Park Road. Very similar menu, but significantly better, fresher food. \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Egg with a vegetable biriyani at a Vegetarian restaurant? What?\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I've only been here twice and I ended up at the doctor both times so now I avoid it like the plague. Never again.\n                                            ", "\n\n                                    I've been to this place a couple of times. This is one review that I would totally agree on.  The serving staff there appear to be uninterested in the job they do and since we don't see what's really going around in the kitchen, one can only assume that the kitchen staff also work with the same lackluster attitude, which affects the quality of food in more ways than one. Now I avoid the place like the plague. \n                                            "], "contact": "Call 011 2822992", "address": "41 Kandewatta Road Nugegoda ", "directions": "To your right on Kandewatta Road which is opposite Wetland Park.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "05:30 PM \u2013 10:30 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "05:30 PM \u2013 10:30 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "05:30 PM \u2013 10:30 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "05:30 PM \u2013 10:30 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "05:30 PM \u2013 10:30 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "05:30 PM \u2013 10:30 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "05:30 PM \u2013 10:30 PM"], "cuisine": ["Indian"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 1000 - Rs. 1500", "dishes": ["Vegetarian"], "overall_rating": "2", "quality_rating": "2", "service_rating": "1", "ambience_rating": "3", "near_by_places_names": ["The K-9", "Urban Wetland Park (Nugegoda)", "Sovereign German Restaurant", "CP's Grill", "Hasara Kitchen"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["86 Nawala Road, Nugegoda", "100 Nawala Road, Colombo", "157 Nawala Road, Nugegoda", "211D, Stanley Thilakarathne Mawatha, Nugegoda", "No: 195 Pagoda Rd, Nugegoda"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 177 m away", " 200 m away", " 231 m away", " 501 m away", " 511 m away"], "similar_places": ["Cosy Restaurant (Jaffna)", "Indo Ceylon Cafe"]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/fat-panda/review-179386", "name": "Fat Panda", "excerpt": "A multi-cuisine casual restaurant off Marine Drive, with a whole range of fusion Asian fare.", "yamu_review": ["Fat Panda is a one-stop-shop for fusion Asian dining. The best part is that you don't have to dress up and you can BYOB. Don't confuse it with another zaftig animal, ", ", which is a bit further along Marine Drive.", "At first glance, the menu seems expensive. But then you realise it's inclusive of pesky taxes and hidden charges and it doesn't seem too bad. We tried an Indonesian Satay (Rs. 1100), a Singapore Chilli Crab (Rs. 1650), and a Pad Thai (Rs. 1300).", "The satay was a hefty portion of 3 thick chicken satays on a bed of pickled vegetables accompanied by a thick home-made herby peanut sauce, and steamed rice topped with caramelized crispy onion. The flavours at play were great, and everything well-prepared, but we thought the pieces of chicken were too thick (which made them a bit dry on the inside).", "Our pad thai on the other hand was excellent. The delicate Thai flavours, with zesty lemongrass and soft, succulent chicken bits made for a delicious dish. This was also fairly large and in my opinion enough for two to share. We'll definitely be coming back for this.", "Our final, greatest dish was the crab. A massive, fiery concoction of crispy sweet-chilli batter, succulent medium shell crab, and chunks of flavour-soaked fresh crab meat, this is one of my favourite crab preparations in the city. Again, I felt this was enough for two people and totally worth shelling out for (heh). Also where are you going to get this quality and quantity of crab for this price?", "The drinks were a tad boring, just a few juices and mocktails. We opted for an Orange Fizz (Rs. 400), which was basically orange juice and soda, and a Jungle Cooler (Rs. 500) which was a pina colada without alcohol.\u00a0", "The waitstaff were great throughout our experience. Swift, friendly, and efficient. We were pleasantly surprised at how quickly the food came out despite being prepared fresh (although this is partially because we were the only people there). They also knew their way around the menu.", "The restaurant commandeers two levels of a small building on the tiny Sea Avenue. The top floor isn't ready yet, but they're planning to create a rooftop area for small events etc. As it stands, the decor is quite confused, with plastic wood and brick wallpaper, as well as Emperor Quin's terracotta army and charming newspaper geisha artwork upstairs (even though they don't really serve either Mainland Chinese or Japanese cuisine).", "We sat downstairs for lunch, which was a huge mistake as the room wasn't properly air conditioned and we were\u00a0slowly baking and sweating. Also, the front of the restaurant is on street level and completely glass, so we found ourselves in a greenhouse, subject to staring and soliciting by the people on the road outside. Our only view apart from this was a run down dry cleaners opposite.\u00a0", "The food and service here are excellent. We didn't love the ambience, but who cares about the view when you're elbow-deep in excellent chilli crab? Overall, we'd highly recommend this spot if you want somewhere to have a quiet corkage-free drink and a whole lot of crab.", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Our first dining experience at the brand new Fat Panda in Colpetty.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0dc6\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da9\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dd9  \u0da0\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dca, \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0d82\u0d9c\u0db4\u0dca\u0db4\u0dd6\u0dbb\u0dd4, \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca, \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca  \u0d9a\u0dd1\u0db8 \u0d91\u0d9a \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0d9a\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0d92\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc6\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd4\u0dc2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dca\u0da7\u0ddd\u0dbb\u0db1\u0da7\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca.  \u0d91\u0dc5\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db6\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d85\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca.\n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            Such a great place to chill  \u2764 the food was delicious.\n                                    ", "\n                                            Went there for dinner last evening and got the Nasi Goreng, Stir Fry Shrimp, Hot Butter Cuttlefish and Micky Mouse :D. The food was delicious!  True enough we were the only customers there though but we didn't really care! The food was yum! \n                                    ", "\n                                            Went there for dinner last evening and got the Nasi Goreng, Stir Fry Shrimp, Hot Butter Cuttlefish and Micky Mouse :D. The food was delicious!  True enough we were the only customers there though but we didn't really care! The food was yum! \n                                    ", "\n                                            Great place overall. Food needs to be made more accurately as the original dishes, regardless there's ample flavor\n                                    ", "\n                                            Take away order - Food was tasty and was very authentic. Main Courses had good portions, The shrimp cakes tasted good but quantity was less in my opinion. Need to work on the pricing as it's a little too expensive with contrast to competitors. Work on this and this place could have a lot of potential ahead.\n                                    ", "\n                                            We went around 3pm no one was there.  At least we got good service.  Food is just okay.  Pad Thai did not have the right flavour.   Chicken satays were soft and tender.  Prices are nett including taxes. The place has no ambience though.  Probably won't go there again anytime soon . It is still new though and may pick up in a few months.  \n                                    ", "\n                                            Lol 1100 bucks for satay!? Satay here in Singapore is only about 1$\n                                    ", "\n                                            I went with my brother and family around 4pm not a single soul\n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    could you post the menu please \n                                            ", "\n\n                                    Done! ", " \n                                            "], "contact": "Call 011 7 772772", "address": "30A, Sea Avenue, Colombo 03 ", "directions": "Sea Avenue is just off Marine Drive, the road before Whight & Co.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Asian", "Malay", "Fusion", "South-East Asian"], "price_range": "More than Rs.1500", "dishes": ["Seafood", "Crab"], "overall_rating": "4", "quality_rating": "5", "service_rating": "5", "ambience_rating": "3", "near_by_places_names": ["Vespa Sports Club", "China Town ", "MacMart Shoppers Store", "Indian Spice", "Whight & Co"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["Sea Avenue, Colombo 3", "38, Sea Avenue, Marine Drive, Colombo 03", "31/5, Ground Floor, Sea Avenue (Marine Drive) \r\nColombo 03", "38, Sea Avenue,  (Marine Drive) Colombo 03.", "Marine Drive and Aloe Avenue, Colombo 3"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 10 m away", " 10 m away", " 21 m away", " 25 m away", " 72 m away"], "similar_places": ["Havi Restaurant", "Nihal's (Jetwing Lighthouse Club)"]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/cafe-bagatalle/review-180145", "name": "Cafe Bagatalle", "excerpt": "A great place for some healthy meals.", "yamu_review": ["For every 5 new restaurants, there's one healthy spot opening up in Colombo. Cafe Bagatalle's got a range of intercontinental cuisine with a Sri Lankan twist. The food was\u00a0absolutely delicious and\u00a0vegetarian-friendly.", "Their menu is pretty extensive and they've mentioned all the nutrients below each dish which is cool if you're counting calories.", "We got a Brochette of Mozzarella (Rs. 490) which had 395 calories. It was accompanied by a saffron risotto and grilled vegetables. The risotto was delicious and cheesy which blended very well with the vegetables. The veggies\u00a0were fresh and seasoned\u00a0properly. The portion was really filling, but I don't think you can call anything healthy after putting\u00a0that much cheese in it. However, texture and flavour wise it was top notch.\u00a0", "We also tried the Penne with Roasted Prawns (Rs. 725) which was 120 calories. It was absolute heaven. The pasta was cooked well and the pesto and chilli oil were a great combo which gave the pasta the spice we Sri Lankans can't live without. There were about 6 or 7 big prawns which are a lot more than you would normally get in a pasta dish at that price. The portion was enough for one and wasn't as filling as the risotto. \u00a0", "For dessert, we got the Hot Brownie and Vanilla Ice Cream with Crunchy Nuts (Rs. 300). It was worth every penny. What's more, it was made with gluten free kurakkan. Of course, it didn't taste like your normal\u00a0chocolate brownies, but that doesn't mean it was bad. \u00a0It was gooey and a lot less sweet which was great because the sweetness of the ice cream balanced out the flavours.\u00a0", "For our drinks, we got a Cafe Latte (Rs. 400) and a Signature Coffee (Rs. 450). The Latte was served warm and the espresso used definitely came across as a bit bitter. The signature coffee was sadly just an iced coffee, although the waiter did tell us that\u00a0before we ordered. It was your normal iced coffee, sweet and tasty, so why\u00a0they would charge Rs. 450 for it is beyond me.\u00a0", "The staff was friendly and accommodating. There was no problem with our orders and the place wasn't that crowded when we went so the food arrived fairly quickly.\u00a0", "The interior of the cafe is small and cosy with wooden tables and chairs and a lot of natural light. The cafe is\u00a0surrounded by a lot of greenery and they also have a great fitness theme going on where you can sit on stability balls or spinners while you enjoy your meal, which is kinda cool.", "It might not be as healthy as ", ", but it's got good food, relatively mid-range prices, and a super central location on Duplication Road! They also deliver now, so call them to find out more.", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Cafe Bagatalle's got a range of intercontinental cuisine with a Sri Lankan twist.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3 \u0d9a\u0dd1\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dda\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0db6\u0dd3\u0dbd\u0dcf, \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d91\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0db8 \u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d95\u0db1\u0dda \u0db1\u0db8\u0dca, \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0dc6\u0dda \u0db6\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dbd\u0dda \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dda \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd0\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd3\u0db4\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca.\n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": ["\n                                            Dropped in yesterday. Just scouted a bit inside Hameedias and entered. A nice, cosy charming place. Probably the cheapest three course meal ever in Colombo! For Rs999 combo per person you get to choose a salad, a soup and a main. I was quite flabbergasted with the price and the options you could choose as if you do order the above individually the prices are different and certainly total ads more than Rs 999, i wonder if its a costing error or a promotion ?? However lovely salad, a nice creamy soup and delicious pasta!. You can view the open kitchen and the two chefs were busy going about the operation and everything was served within the a reasonable gap. ", "\r\n", "\r\nCafe bagatelle is a gem! With eating quality food is costing a fortune with those taxes and service charges added, this is one hell of a steal!\n                                    ", "\n                                            Love this Cafe.  Good food at very reasonable prices.  Service is good. \n                                    "], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    Love this little Cafe.  Very fresh and high quality food at very reasonable prices.  Service is good.  \n                                            "], "contact": "Call 011 3 818815", "address": "No. 18 Bagatalle Road\r\nColombo Sri Lanka ", "directions": "\n                                    ", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["07:00 AM \u2013 10:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 10:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 10:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 10:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 10:0