{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/blue-lagoon-jetwing-lagoon/review-205435", "name": "Blue Lagoon (Jetwing Lagoon)", "excerpt": "Blue Lagoon restaurant serves nice and surprisingly affordable food in a magnificent venue.", "yamu_review": ["Blue Lagoon, Jetwing Lagoon's restaurant, impresses with its exquisite architecture and decoration,\u00a05-star service and prime location\u00a0on Negombo lagoon bank. The food is not that exciting though.\u00a0", "Blue Lagoon's menu offers a large range of Sri Lankan, Asian and Western inspired snacks,\u00a0mains and drinks. Unless you or your crew is extremely picky, you should find something to munch on or to sip in.", "Food and drinks are well executed and presented and they surprisingly\u00a0come\u00a0at a reasonable price. If you choose wisely and stay away from the booze, you can have a decent meal for about Rs. 1,200 or even less. Some substantial\u00a0options such as burgers\u00a0or pastas are priced around Rs. 800. It's not as cheap as a filling meal at your usual ", "\u00a0but in such a location, you'd expect the bill to be inflated.", "While we were waiting for our mains\u00a0to come out of the kitchen - which didn't take long by the way - we were given a complementary basket of breads with olive oil and\u00a0roasted onion cream. Nice touch.", "We opted for the Rosemary Pork Cutlets with Fruit Kebabs (Rs. 1,300). It was refined and generous. The two pork cutlets were nicely cooked and seasoned. As stated on the menu, they came with a side of\u00a0roasted pineapple and mango on a skewer. The sweet and salty combo worked really well with the meat. And one of the best parts of having some roasted fruits as a side instead of rice or fries, is that we weren't feeling stuffed.", "The Spaghetti Bolognese (Rs. 850) came\u00a0deconstructed with the Bolognese sauce and parmegiano on the side. It enabled us to check that each\u00a0element\u00a0was well executed: pastas were al dente, the sauce was meaty and tasty and the parmegiano, well...\u00a0cheesy? All together, it obviously worked well. Again, the portion\u00a0was generous.\u00a0", "We also ordered the Vegetarian Spring Rolls with Asian Noodles (Rs. 750). The spring rolls dough was nice, fluffy and flavoursome. The well cooked noodles were served with veggies, in a kind of a chop suey sauce. I personally found the noodle dish\u00a0a bit boring but to be fair, I'm not a chop suey person.", "All in all, the food was nice and we couldn't fault anything but it didn't wow us as much as the surroundings.\u00a0", "As for drinks, we went for a Mango juice at around Rs. 500 and it was worth every penny. So good we gulped it as soon as it landed on the table and therefore we don't have any picture of it. They use natural and fresh mangoes\u00a0so the drink didn't need any sugar. One of the best mango juices we've ever had.", "We also had a round of Espressos at Rs. 350 each. The espresso\u00a0was an honest one and\u00a0fulfilled its purpose of waking us up for the drive back to Colombo.", "Designed\u00a0by the legendary architect Geoffrey Bawa\u00a0and operated by Jetwing, this place is obviously charming and luxurious. There's nothing not to like in the design of the restaurant and, more generally, of the hotel. Jetwing did a good job in keeping the decoration simple,\u00a0enhancing this way the architecture and\u00a0the natural surroundings.", "The restaurant is vast, and\u00a0in addition to\u00a0the\u00a0spacious dining room, it has a comfy lounge and a narrow terrace on the lagoon. Almost empty on the day we visited, the place felt very private and exclusive.", "The star here is definitely the lagoon. Try to get here before the sunset to enjoy the soothing sight of the scenery from the golden hour to the pitch-dark night when fairy lights illuminate the majestic tree in front of the restaurant.", "Service is 5-star. The staff is attentive without being disruptive at any time. They let you chill and wander around as much as you want and don't pressure you to leave or overconsume once you're done with your meal or drinks. We've easily spent half a day there on the stormy day we came in.", "Staff is also very efficient and orders didn't take long to reach the\u00a0table.", "More than the food, it's the 5-star atmosphere and the stunning view on the lagoon that's really special here."], "user_reviews": [], "user_comments": [], "contact": "Call +94 31 2233777", "address": "Pamunugama Road, Thalahena, Negombo ", "directions": "In Thalahena, on a thin stretch of land next to the Negombo lagoon.", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Western", "Sri Lankan"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 500 - Rs. 1000", "dishes": ["Meats", "Seafood", "Pasta", "Salad", "Vegetarian", "Rice And Curry", "Pork", "Bready", "Sandwiches", "Coffee", "Alcoholic", "Cocktails"], "overall_rating": "4", "quality_rating": "3", "service_rating": "5", "ambience_rating": "5", "near_by_places_names": ["Jetwing Lagoon ", "Sasha Food Court (Kurana)", "Negombo Fort & Lagoon ", "Negombo Fish Market ", "IceBear Century Caf\u00e9 (Negombo) "], "near_by_places_addresses": ["Pamunugama Road, Negombo", "584, Colombo road, Kurana", "Selby Road, Negombo", "Selby Road, Negombo (west side) ", "25 Main Street, Negombo"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 55 m away", " 4.36 km away", " 4.59 km away", " 4.74 km away", " 4.77 km away"], "similar_places": ["Earl\u2019s Passikudah", "Podi Hoona - The Little Gecko Luxury Campsite"]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/double-cheese-coffee-dine/review-204895", "name": "Double Cheese Coffee & Dine", "excerpt": "Double Cheese Coffee & Dine is one of the finest family restaurants in Dehiwala area that dishes out a range of Sri Lankan and European food for an affordable price.  ", "yamu_review": ["For the past few months, the restaurant scene in the suburbs of Dehiwala - Mount Lavinia area has been on a skyrocket. A bunch of new spots have opened up, and us foodies couldn\u2019t be happier. Double Cheese Coffee & Dine on\u00a0Hill Street is one such restaurant, that\u00a0we stumbled across\u00a0wholly by accident.", "The menu at Double Cheese Coffee & Dine is quite extensive, so you\u2019ll have a lot to choose from. They serve a range of burgers, submarines, kottu, rice-centred\u00a0specialties, pasta, lasagna\u00a0and even pizza. They also do rice and curry for lunch and at Rs. 250 a packet, they\u2019re only available for take away. As for drinks, they\u2019ve got coffee, tea, milkshakes, smoothies and fresh juices.", "We ordered a portion of\u00a0Seafood Fried Rice (Rs. 450 for S),\u00a0a plate of Hot Butter Cuttlefish (Rs. 700) and\u00a0Creamy Penne Pasta with Chicken (Rs. 400).", "The seafood fried rice was absolutely delicious. The\u00a0Basmati rice was cooked well, properly seasoned and not too oily. It had plenty of cuttlefish and prawns tossed in with pieces of eggs, carrots, and spring onions. For couple more hundred bucks\u00a0you can get the large portion of this rice. The small one was easily sharable between two people.", "The hot butter cuttlefish was a tad salty for my taste. It was crunchy, chewy,\u00a0adequately spiced and flavoursome, but tasted like a re-fried and not freshly made. This is not the worst HBC, but we\u2019ve had better.", "Perfectly cooked penne pasta with decadently creamy texture, this dish was our instant favourite. It was garnished with bell pepper, which didn\u2019t do much to the flavour but added colour to the dish. Although we\u2019d prefer more minced chicken on this,\u00a0it was still super delish. It came with a side of toasted bread.", "For drinks, we got a Dark Chocolate Latte (Rs. 400) and a Falooda (Rs. 390). The latte was\u00a0very chocolatey\u00a0and had a rich coffee flavour that comes through the fluffy foamy milk.", "The falooda on the other hand was slightly too sweet, but had the other basic elements in the right balance. Topped with a scoop of vanilla ice cream and sprinkled with ", " (poppy seeds), this is a good thirst quencher to beat the heat.", "The staff at Double Cheese Coffee & Dine is very attentive and friendly. They\u2019re more than happy to assist you to choose the best food that goes with your appetite. Our food and drinks took around 15 minutes to arrive, which is impressive considering the large number of customers they had in the restaurant at the peak hour.", "We liked the ambience here. It\u2019s spacious enough to comfortably accommodate at least thirty customers and has a pleasant vibe. According to the manager, the restaurant gets booked all the time for birthday parties and family dinners.", "It\u2019s been only 5 - 6 months since their opening but as we could see, it has already become the crowd\u2019s favourite. They\u2019re affordable, tasty and efficient, so if you\u2019re around Dehiwala area looking for a good meal within a budget, this is just the place to be.", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    Double Cheese Coffee & Dine on Hill Street serves up some good food for a reasonable cost.\n                                                                                                                            ", "\n                                                                                                                                    ", "\n                                                                \n                                                                                                                                    \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dda \u0d85\u0db4\u0da7 \u0dbd\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0db3\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0d85\u0dad\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7, \u0da9\u0db6\u0dbd\u0dca \u0da0\u0dd3\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dc6\u0dd3 \u0d87\u0db1\u0dca\u0da9\u0dca \u0da9\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dda \u0d9a\u0dd1\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dda\u0dbd \u0dc4\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca.\n                                                                                                                            "], "user_reviews": [], "user_comments": ["\n\n                                    Double Cheese Coffee & Dine \u0d91\u0d9a \u0daf\u0dd1\u0db1\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd9 \u0dba\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0db6\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dbd\u0dcf.\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0daf\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dd1\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd1\u0db8 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0daf\u0da7\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dcf.Service \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db8\u0dba\u0dd2.\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0db4\u0dd1\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd9 \u0dba\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1.", "\n", "\nThank You \u0dba\u0db8\u0dd4\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026\u2026", "\n", "\n\n                                            "], "contact": "Call 011 4 363625", "address": "No. 205, Hill Street, Dehiwala ", "directions": "From Dehiwala junction, turn on to Hill Street, and drive for 850 meters. It's at the left hand side of the road, right in front of the Healthguard pharmacy. ", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM", "07:00 AM \u2013 11:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Italian", "Sri Lankan", "Sri Lankan Chinese", "Fast Food", "European"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 500 - Rs. 1000", "dishes": ["Pasta", "Kottu", "Biriyani", "Rice And Curry", "Fried Rice", "Fish And Chips", "Cuttlefish", "Sandwiches", "Pizza", "Coffee", "Tea", "Milkshakes", "Faluda"], "overall_rating": "4", "quality_rating": "4", "service_rating": "4", "ambience_rating": "4", "near_by_places_names": ["Khalid's Computer Solutions", "KGN Burgers on Wheels", "Moreish ", "Burger Hut", "Cafe Asiana"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["28, Siriwardena Road, Dehiwala", "Hill Street, Dehiwala (After Dharmarama Rd)", "123/1, Anagarika Dharmapala Mawatha, Dehiwala", "126, D.B. Jayathilaka Mawatha (Hill Street), Dehiwala", "97, Hill Street, Dehiwala"], "near_by_places_distances": [" 328 m away", " 332 m away", " 571 m away", " 631 m away", " 680 m away"], "similar_places": ["Earl\u2019s Passikudah", "Lak Rasa Caterers "]}
{"url": "https://www.yamu.lk/place/spisia/review-221907", "name": "Spisia", "excerpt": "Spisia is one of the  most popular restaurants in Piliyandala area, that serves up some good Sri Lankanised Chinese food. ", "yamu_review": ["Spisia\u00a0is one of the most popular eateries in Piliyandala. They do some decent Chinese food with a Sri Lankan twist, for an affordable price tag.", "The menu at Spisia is quite extensive, but you\u2019ll have a lot to choose from. We ordered a small portion of their Nasi Goreng at Rs. 640, Sweet and Sour Pork (Rs. 560) and Hot Butter Mushroom (Rs.440).", "The Nasi Goreng was properly spiced and had a very bright yellowish appearance. Tossed in with some prawns and roasted chicken, the rice was cooked to perfection and wasn\u2019t too oily either.", "Crispy, crunchy, adequately spiced and flavorsome; the Hot Butter Mushroom was our instant favorite. The portion size was easily enough to feed three people, which was pretty decent for that price. It wasn\u2019t good as the ones we got at ", ", or ", " but it was on the tastier side. But still, it tasted\u00a0re-fried, and not freshly made.", "The Sweet and Sour Pork dish at Spisia didn't impress us. We usually expect the sweet and sour pork to be a curry, with crispy bits of pork, beautifully blended with onions, bell pepper/capsicum in a savory pineapple sauce that anyone is guaranteed to love. But here, it was just some deep fried battered pork stripes, with a side of sweet and sour sauce. The batter was kind of soggy, and the pork was slightly undercooked. But the sauce itself was delightful, as it had the sweet and sour elements perfectly balanced in a very light texture.\u00a0", "Spisia provides a very comfortable and casual environment for their customers. The place is well-maintained and gives an ideal setting for family lunches/dinners, or a gathering of friends. They\u2019ve got a TV hanging on the corner, so you can enjoy their food while catching up on a game, or listening to some music.", "The service was a bit slow at the beginning, which was quite disappointing considering that we\u00a0were the only customers there. We had to walk up to the billing counter to ask for a menu, and again to place the order as no one came to take it while we were sitting at our table.", "Our order\u00a0took around 15 minutes to arrive, and\u00a0we noticed that they get a lot of take-out\u00a0orders from the residents\u00a0around.", "Spisia is a good restaurant to grab some Sri Lankanised Chinese food if you're in the area. We're not entirely unhappy about our experience, but the service and the food could be improved a bit."], "user_reviews": [], "user_comments": [], "contact": "Call 0777212125", "address": "No. 75, Kottawa Road, Piliyandala. ", "directions": "\n                        ", "opening_days": ["MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY", "SATURDAY", "SUNDAY"], "opening_hours": ["11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "06:00 PM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "06:00 PM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "06:00 PM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "06:00 PM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "06:00 PM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "06:00 PM \u2013 11:00 PM", "11:00 AM \u2013 03:00 PM", "06:00 PM \u2013 11:00 PM"], "cuisine": ["Sri Lankan Chinese"], "price_range": "Between Rs. 1000 - Rs. 1500", "dishes": ["Eggs", "Fried Rice", "Beef", "Pork", "Chicken", "Fish", "Cuttlefish", "Fruit Juice"], "overall_rating": "3", "quality_rating": "3", "service_rating": "3", "ambience_rating": "4", "near_by_places_names": ["My Sister's Kitchen ", "Sweet Layers", "Shelter4Homeless", "Fat Guy BBQ", "Courage Compassion Commitment (CCC) Foundation"], "near_by_places_addresses": ["53, New City Garden, Gadabuwana, Piliyandala (Delivery) ", "No. 02, Nilani Gardens, Bokundara, Piliyandala", "No: 353 Welvita Road, Piliyandala", "12 Ferry Road, Piliyandala", "National Cancer Institute, Maharagama"], "near_by_pla